non-financial quality of a firm, which may reflect value to investors either through higher expected profit or lower risk. In this paper, we focus on the latter by exploring whether ESG score has any impact on the credit rating of firms due to the risk mitigation effect. Ordered logistic regressions were applied on a panel dataset of listed companies in Shanghai and Tokyo Stock Exchanges over 2009\\u20132018. The results suggest that only in Japan, having ESG coverage is greatly associated with being awarded higher credit rating. However, just the environmental and governance pillars positively affect the Japanese firms\\u2019 credit ratings, while the social pillar shows negative effect.\"));\n}\n;\nMDXContent.isMDXComponent = true;","fields":{"slug":"/dp/129/esg-and-creditworthiness-two-contrary-evidence-from-major-asian-markets/","collection":"dp","shorturl":"/dp/129/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"ESG and Creditworthiness: Two Contrary Evidence from Major Asian Markets","subtitle":null,"series":null,"authors":["Natthawat Jamprasert","Pornpitchaya Kuwalairat","Narapong Srivisal","Jananya Sthienchoak"],"date":"2020-03-31T00:00:00.000Z","updated":null,"cover":null,"excerpt":null,"bibliography":null,"topics":null,"tags":null,"layout":null,"pdf":{"publicURL":"/static/76cecea343bf7b7c55dcb29fedeb0251/pier_dp_129.pdf"}},"authors":[{"frontmatter":{"memberid":"Jananya Sthienchoak","title":"Jananya Sthienchoak","org":"cu","email":"jananya@cbs.chula.ac.th","image":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","backgroundColor":"#888868","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/3e8e9a09ca31822649ec7b64f3ad74ed/dd515/profile.jpg","srcSet":"/static/3e8e9a09ca31822649ec7b64f3ad74ed/6ac16/profile.jpg 50w,\n/static/3e8e9a09ca31822649ec7b64f3ad74ed/e07e1/profile.jpg 100w,\n/static/3e8e9a09ca31822649ec7b64f3ad74ed/dd515/profile.jpg 200w,\n/static/3e8e9a09ca31822649ec7b64f3ad74ed/47930/profile.jpg 400w","sizes":"(min-width: 200px) 200px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static